18/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski and Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski met Saturday (17 January) to discuss the progress of reforms in the Macedonian defence sector. 
They decided to hold two meetings next week to discuss the plans and projects for military reforms in light of the forthcoming NATO summit in Istanbul. 
They will also discuss the appointment of a new army chief of staff. 
(MIA, A1 TV - 17/01/04)
